    {
      "title": "Install steps",
      "description": "1. Create a kind cluster:\n\n>> kind create cluster\n\n>> kubectl cluster-info --context kind-kind\n\n\n2. Install Conductor agent:\n\n`kubectl apply -f \"link to manifest\"`\n\n3. Check progress of pods:\n\n>> kubectl get pods --all-namespaces\n\n4. Install Redis:\n\n>> helm repo add bitnami https://charts.bitnami.com/bitnami\n\n>> helm repo update\n\n>> helm install redis bitnami/redis --set image.tag=6.2\n\n5. Install Kafka:\n\n>> helm install kafka oci://registry-1.docker.io/bitnamicharts/kafka --version 22.1.5 --set \"provisioning.topics[0].name=events-topic\" --set \"provisioning.topics[0].partitions=1\" --set \"persistence.size=250Mi\"\n\n6. Install the services and Dapr components:\n\n>> kubectl apply -f k8s/\n\n7. Forward the port:\n\n>> kubectl port-forward svc/pizza-store 8080:80\n\n8. Run the app:\n\n[http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)\n\nor run ddosify to make multiple requests:\n\n>> bash run.sh\n\nDelete the cluster once you're done with the demos:\n\n>> kind delete cluster"
    }
  ]
